
[1]judiciously

   JUDI'CIOUSLY, adv. With good judgment; with discretion or wisdom;
   skillfully.

   Longinus has judiciously preferred the sublime genius that sometimes
   errs,to the middling or indifferent one, which makes few faults, but
   seldom rises to excellence.
